HEADWORD: Forefront
<hw>Fore"front`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Foremost part or
place.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Set ye Uriah in the <qex>forefront</qex> of the hottest
battle.</q> <rj><qau>2 Sam. xi. 15.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Socrates, Plato, Aristotle, standing in the <qex>forefront</qex>
for all time, the masters of those who know.</q> <rj><qau>J. C.
Shairp.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foregame</ent>⟦br⟧
